      "span_text": "In 2014, a prospective study including 95 patients with painful hip or knee arthroplasties in which the authors evaluated 16 biomarkers involved in the immune reaction after a PJI. Five of them (α-defensin 1.3, neutrophil elastase 2, bactericidal/permeabilityincreasing protein, neutrophil gelatinase-associated lipocalin and lactoferrin) showed a 100% sensitivity and specificity in diagnosing PJI [CITATION_1] .",
